content.description: Sit start low on bad, sharp crimps with low feet. Stand up into a crimpy left-hand undercling and then move your right up to a pocket edge below the lip of the top. Slap your right hand up further to the top. Move your left hand up higher on the undercling edge and then bump your right hand to a good jug at the top. Top out from there.
content.location: In the middle of The Fin. Sit start down low. Climb straight up from the start and work slightly left to the top after that.

content.description: Start at the start of Six-Gilled Shark and work into the regular start of I'm Not A Seal.
content.location: Starts below the regular start of I'm Not A Seal on the start of Six-Gilled Shark.

content.description: Sit start on the far right of the fin in some pockets and edges. Slap up to the lip and continue along the lip to the very top.
content.location: Starts on the far right corner of the fin and then works left to the top along the lip.

content.description: Starts on the furthest left edge of The Fin, work up the arete to top out.
content.location: Starts in the furthest left corner of The Fin on the arete and works up it to the top.

content.description: An interesting shaped boulder in the Trailside boulder area. Slightly overhung and has a couple of cool, hard routes.
